  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2022-12-08",
    "date": "2023-09-13T18:52:21Z",
    "text": "American Safety And Fairness through Expedited Removal Act of 2022 or the American SAFER Act of 2022\n\nThis bill expands the classes of non-U.S. nationals (aliens under federal law) who are subject to expedited removal (i.e., removal from the United States without further hearing or review).\n\nSpecifically, the bill nullifies a 2004 Department of Homeland Security (DHS) rule\u00a0that generally limits expedited removal to certain situations, such as for non-U.S. nationals encountered within 14 days of entry into the United States without inspection and within 100 miles of a U.S. international land border.\n\nThe bill also (1) prohibits DHS from implementing a rule that limits expedited removal based on how far a non-U.S. national was from the border when encountered or apprehended, and (2) modifies the relevant statute to state that expedited removal authority applies regardless of where the non-U.S. national was encountered or apprehended."
  },
